# =============================================================================
# Clerk Authentication (REQUIRED for Journal feature only)
# =============================================================================
# WHY CLERK?
# The PS-LANG™ Journal is a dual-licensed premium feature that requires user
# authentication, role-based access control (RBAC), and end-to-end encryption
# for secure prompt history storage. Clerk provides:
#
# - User authentication (sign-up/sign-in/sign-out)
# - Role management (super_admin, admin, reviewer, alpha_tester, user)
# - Public metadata storage for RBAC without exposing sensitive data
# - Session management & JWT tokens for secure API calls
# - Pre-built UI components that integrate with our design system
#
# HOW IT WORKS IN PS-LANG:
# 1. Users sign up → Clerk assigns default 'user' role
# 2. Super admins can upgrade roles via /admin/roles dashboard
# 3. Middleware checks role permissions before allowing route access:
#    - /journal → admin, reviewer, super_admin only
#    - /playground → open to alpha_testers too
#    - /admin → super_admin only
# 4. Client-side encryption uses user's password to protect journal entries
# 5. Private keys stored encrypted in Clerk user metadata
#
# NOTE: If you're only using PS-LANG core syntax (no Journal), you can skip
# Clerk setup and remove auth-related routes.
#
# Get your keys from: https://dashboard.clerk.com/last-active?path=api-keys
# 1. Create a new application at https://dashboard.clerk.com/
# 2. Open the API Keys page
# 3. Copy your Publishable Key and Secret Key below
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your_key_here
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_your_secret_key_here

# Clerk Routes (customize if needed)
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=/sign-in
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=/sign-up
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_IN_URL=/journal
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_UP_URL=/journal

# =============================================================================
# Anthropic Claude API (OPTIONAL - only if using AI-assisted features)
# =============================================================================
# PS-LANG core syntax doesn't require this. Only needed if you want:
# - AI-powered prompt suggestions in the playground
# - Automatic zone detection/tagging
# - Journal entry analysis
#
# Get your API key from: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-your_key_here

# =============================================================================
# Email & Admin (OPTIONAL - only if you want feedback/newsletter features)
# =============================================================================
# Used for:
# - Sending feedback form submissions to your email
# - Newsletter signups
# - Admin notifications
#
# If you don't need these features, you can skip this section entirely.
#
# Get your API key from: https://resend.com/api-keys
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_your_key_here
# RESEND_AUDIENCE_ID=your_audience_id_here
# RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=hello@yourdomain.com
# ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@yourdomain.com

# =============================================================================
# Convex Database (OPTIONAL - for persistent data storage)
# =============================================================================
# Convex is a real-time database for storing:
# - User feedback submissions
# - Newsletter subscribers
# - Alpha signup data
# - Journal entries (encrypted)
# - .psl file storage
#
# Setup instructions:
# 1. Install: npm install convex
# 2. Run: npx convex dev (opens browser for auth)
# 3. Copy the deployment URL to NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL below
#
# Get started at: https://www.convex.dev/
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL=https://your-deployment.convex.cloud

